      "body": "<p><strong>Source queued:</strong> https://libguides.com.edu/c.php?g=649524&amp;p=4555063.</p><p><strong>Source type:</strong> Certification Training. <strong>Class-maker credibility tag:</strong> Primary.</p><p><strong>Source URL:</strong> <a href=\"https://libguides.com.edu/c.php?g=649524&amp;p=4555063\">https://libguides.com.edu/c.php?g=649524&amp;p=4555063</a></p><p>Open Access - Texas Independence - LibGuides at COM Library Skip to Main Content Articles &amp; Media Books &amp; eBooks About COM Library Guides COM Library LibGuides Social &amp; Behavioral Texas Independence Open Access Search this Guide Search Texas Independence Learn how Texas won its independence. Introduction Books &amp; eBooks Articles Media Open Access Top Open Access Images &amp; Maps More Sources Top Open Access Top websites, primary sources, or media&amp;nbsp;that are open access and free for anyone, no COM account required. Avalon Project: Texas From Independence to Annexation 1836-1846 Texas State Library and Archives Commission : Texas Declaration of Independence Texas State Library and Archives Commission : The Battle of San Jacinto UT Perry-Castañeda Map Collection: The Defense of the Alamo, February 23 - March 6, 1836 Images &amp; Maps Access images and maps that are open access and free for anyone, no COM account required. Some of these images and maps are also primary sources.&amp;nbsp; A New Map Of Texas, With The Contiguous American &amp; Mexican States by J.H. Young. Philadelphia: Published by S. Augustus Mitchell. 1836. UT Perry-Castañeda Map Collection: San Jacinto Battlefield Map by Henry McArdle - 1836 UT Perry-Castañeda Map Collection: The Defense of the Alamo, February 23 - March 6, 1836 UT Perry-Castañeda Map Collection: The Major Movements of Texan and Mexican Military Forces, February - April, 1836 More Sources More&amp;nbsp;open access sources can be freely accessed by anyone, no COM account required. Avalon Project: Texas From Independence to Annexation 1836-1846 Digital History: The Texas Revolution Son of the South : Republic of Texas Texas State Historical Association: Texas Revolution Texas State Library and Archives Commission: Proclamation of Sam Houston, A Call for Volunteers, December 12, 1835 Texas State Library and Archives Commission: Republic of Texas Texas State Library and Archives Commission: Texas Declaration of Independence Texas State Library and Archives Commission: The Battle of San Jacinto Texas State Library and Archives Commission: The Battle of the Alamo &amp;lt;&amp;lt; Previous: Media Last Updated: Mar 30, 2026 11:48 AM URL: https://libguides.com.edu/TexasInd Print Page Library Staff Login Report a problem Subjects: Texas History Tags: american history history military texas texas history Articles &amp; Media Books &amp; eBooks Guides About COM Library © 2026 COM Library 1200 Amburn Road, Texas City, Texas 77591 409-933-8448 . FAX 409-933-8030 This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International License</p><div class=\"source-quality\"><p><strong>Credibility ranking:</strong> High. <strong>Reliability ranking:</strong> High.</p><p><strong>Information-literacy finding:</strong> Readable source text was available during generation. Use it for supported claims, and corroborate statistics, forecasts, or disputed points.</p></div>"
